.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-8-15::.
4 different games are played: backgammon, mah-jongg, chess, snooker
There are 4 different nationalities: turkish, brazilian, australian, malaysian
 1. the malaysian is somewhere to the left of the australian##5
 2. the person playing snooker is not to the left of the person playing chess##8
 3. the person playing backgammon is the australian##1
 4. the australian is not to the right of the brazilian##8
 5. the malaysian is on the right of the person playing mah-jongg##1
 6. the brazilian is somewhere to the right of the person playing chess##5
 7. the brazilian is on the far left or far right##3
 8. the person playing backgammon is not to the right of the australian##8
 9. the brazilian is not to the left of the person playing backgammon##8
10. the person playing mah-jongg is not to the left of the turkish##8

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1     |     2      |     3      |    4     |
| Game          | mah-jongg    | chess | backgammon | snooker |
| Nationality   | turkish | malaysian  | australian     | brazilian    |

